      children: "3.1.\tFinancial and political instability"
    }), "\n", _jsx(_components.p, {
      children: "Over the last decade, the Turkish energy sector has struggled with an array of financial and regulatory challenges. First, national energy companies have been saddled with dollar-denominated debt, and the depreciation of the lira has made servicing these loans an increasing burden. Second, there is a lack of clear eligibility criteria for generation licenses, especially for solar and wind plants. And the absence of long-term market visibility leads to challenges securing project financing. Loans often require substantial equity investment, which directly affects domestic investors."
    }), "\n", _jsx(_components.p, {
